reviews.review_text:
Get this one! This is the better of the two auds for this show, and to my ears, sounds better than the soundboard with the most reviews (as I type).

The show -- what can I say?  It's one of my favorite shows of the 80's (at least prior to fall 89).  It's even better than the setlist suggests.  Let It Grow is possibly the best stand-alone version, long, intricate, and even a little exploratory towards the end (although Colgate 77 is quite a rousing rendition).  Slipknot has stunning interplay among Jerry, Brent, and Phil, although Bob is not to be heard -- either his volume was turned down or he sat out the Slipknot.  Bob comes back with major contributions for Franklin's.  Then comes the sweetest, dreamiest Playin' you'll hear post-77.  After one of the best D>S segments, Stills comes out and, while his voice is shredded, still sets the place on fire.  The rest is well-played, though nothing special.  Stills comes back for Not Fade Away, but I'll take a 77 version anytime.  Still, it's rare you get such a strong 1st AND second set, particularly post 77.

forgot to mention:  The Franklin's may be a best-ever, in fact so might the entire HSF
You want this one This 'Wilma' source has better levels than the other 'Wilma' source, get this one.
